Bootstrapping for UX/HF Researchers
This repository is for UX and Human Factors (HF) researchers who want a simple setup to get started with data analysis and workflows in R. Whether you’re cleaning data, running statistical analyses, or creating visualizations, this project provides a basic framework to build on.
 
What’s Included?
•	main.R: The main R script for processing data and performing analysis.
•	data/: A folder to organize datasets: 
o	raw/: For unprocessed data.
o	processed/: For cleaned or analyzed data.
o	example.csv: A sample dataset to test the script.
•	README.md: This file, with details about the repository.
•	LICENSE: Information about the open-source license.
 
How to Use This
1.	Clone this repository:
2.	git clone https://github.com/mohsen-rafiei/Bootstrapping.git
3.	cd Bootstrapping
4.	Set up your data:
o	Place raw datasets in the data/raw/ folder.
5.	Run the main script:
Open main.R in your preferred R environment (RStudio or any IDE) and follow the instructions in the script.
6.	Processed datasets and results will be saved in the data/processed/ folder.
 
Purpose
This repository is designed to save time and effort by providing a simple framework for UX and HF research projects. It’s lightweight and easy to customize for your specific needs.
 
Contributing
If you’d like to contribute, feel free to open an issue or submit a pull request. Suggestions and improvements are always welcome.
 
